</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C0B36EEFF80E25DFCE2F9F1D6AE7085" blockId="3.[827,1443,1044,1894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Ossification of the angular, coronoid and parietal begin in phases III and IV. The coronoid starts to ossify from the medial side and the parietal from the lateral side.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C0B36EEFF80E25BFCE2F97CD4197382" blockId="3.[827,1443,1044,1894]" lastBlockId="5.[163,779,1433,1884]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="304" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">In phase V, ossification of the maxilla, exoccipital and angular begins. The maxilla starts to ossify from the medial side, the exoccipital from the posterior side and the angular from the anterior side. Ossification of the premaxilla and dentary is advanced, and several teeth have developed on these bones.</paragraph>
<caption id="48CB6666FF87E25AFF48FD31D7577546" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530544" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6530544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530544/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="303" startId="4.[145,223,697,719]" targetBox="[305,1265,198,655]" targetPageId="4">
